<FIRST>r a PM-ObitWaldorf     05-10 0101</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Obit Waldorf,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Stunt Pilot Dolores Waldorf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dolores Waldorf, a pioneering aviator who
was an original member of Amelia Earhart's 99ers, died of a stroke.
She was 88.
   Waldorf died Monday at Merritt Hospital.
   Waldorf, a stunt flier, was a friend of Earhart, whose 99ers was
made up of 99 famed women pilots in the United States.
   Waldorf performed in barnstorming shows up and down California.
   She also founded the Monarch Flying Service in the early 1930s
and was an instructor for hundreds of pilots who served in World
War II, according to her husband, Howard.
</TEXT>
