<FIRST>r i PM-Uganda     05-10 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Uganda,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kenyan Cattle Rustlers Reportedly Kill 60 Ugandans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 50 heavily armed Kenyan rustlers
killed at least 60 civilians and stole nearly 200 cattle and sheep
in northeastern Uganda, the state newspaper reported today.
   New Vision said two Kenyan helicopter gunships crossed into
Uganda as Ugandan soldiers chased the raiders back across the
border. It did not say whether the helicopters fired at the
pursuing troops.
   The area has been the site of several cross-border raids in
recent months by Ugandan and Kenyan tribal warriors who
traditionally raid each other's livestock. Each country accuses the
other of provoking the attacks.
   New Vision said some raiders wore military fatigues during an
attack two weeks ago in Kapchorwa district, 155 miles northeast of
Kampala.
</TEXT>
