<FIRST>r w AM-TreasuryAuction     05-10 0094</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Treasury Auction,80</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rates at Highest Level Since August</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 10-year Treasury notes rose in
Wednesday's auction to the highest level since August.
   The average yield was 9.18 percent, up from 8.91 percent at the
last auction on Feb. 8.
   It was the highest rate since 10-year notes averaged 9.27
percent on Aug. 10. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
9[ percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,964.50.
   A total of $9.53 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$22 billion.
</TEXT>
