<FIRST>r p AM-Giuliani     05-10 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Giuliani,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Candidate Cancels Announcement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former prosecutor Rudolph W. Giuliani canceled
plans to announce his Republican mayoral candidacy Wednesday,
citing the death of city schools Chancellor Richard Green.
   ``Chancellor Green was a hard-working public servant who had
dedicated his career to helping children,'' Giuliani said in a
statement. ``He was a very decent man. New Yorkers are in his
debt.''
   Giuliani, 44, said he was postponing his announcement ``out of
respect for the memory of Chancellor Green and for his family.''
   Campaign spokesman Charles Perkins said Giuliani's announcement
would be rescheduled after Green's funeral arrangements were known.
   Polls have consistently shown Giuliana defeating incumbent Mayor
Edward I. Koch or any other likely Democratic nominee in a
hypothetical matchup.
</TEXT>
