<HEAD>A Look at Pan Am, Northwest Airlines</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Pan Am-Northwest Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a look at Pan American World Airways and Northwest
Airlines, a subsidiary of NWA Inc. Pan Am's parent Pan Am Corp.
announced Tuesday it was considering making an offer for the
much-larger NWA, which already is the target of several takeover
suitors.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>NORTHWEST</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Size: Northwest is the nation's fourth-largest airline.
   Headquarters: Eagan, Minn.
   Employees: 33,700.
   Fleet size: 312.
   Cities served: 111 U.S., 24 foreign, with major markets in the
Midwest, Pacific Northwest and Far East.
   Passengers: about 35 million annually.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>PAN AM</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Size: Pan Am is the nation's eighth-largest airline.
   Headquarters: New York.
   Employees: 22,000.
   Fleet Size, 160 aircraft.
   Cities served: 34 U.S., 68 foreign, with major markets in the
East Coast and Western Europe.
   Passengers: about 18 million annually.
</TEXT>
