<DOCNO> AP890510-0240 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-05-10-89 0152EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     05-10 0099</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Treasury Auction,0104</SECOND>
<HEAD>T-Note Rate Lowest in Seven Months</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on three-year Treasury notes fell in
the government's latest auction to the lowest level since last
November.
   The average yield was 9.12 percent on Tuesday, down from 9.18
percent at the last auction on Feb. 7.
   It was the lowest rate since three-year notes averaged 8.59
percent on Nov. 8. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 9
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,969.10.
   A total of $9.79 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$29.71 billion.
</TEXT>
