<FIRST>r f PM-CupcakeBirthday     05-10 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Cupcake Birthday,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hostess Celebrates Cupcake's 70th Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Though no one knows who invented the original
Hostess cupcake, there's no question D.R. ``Doc'' Rice improved the
treat.
   Rice, 83, injected the creme filling and put the squiggly white
line atop the cupcake's chocolate icing at Continental Baking Co.'s
Detroit plant. He was to return to Detroit today to celebrate the
cupcake's 70th birthday.
   The original cupcake from Hostess came out May 10, 1919. It was
made of devil's food cake and hand-covered with vanilla or
chocolate icing.
   Wartime rationing had restricted the amount and quality of some
ingredients, especially sugar and chocolate. Rice's changes led to
the widespread popularity of the snack.
   Hostess, owned by St. Louis-based Continental Baking, sold 400
million cupcakes last year.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
